The core problem is the premature loop termination condition. When `nb_fd_epoll > 1`, the function stops waiting for messages, potentially leaving messages unprocessed. This creates a race condition where message queue events might be missed if other file descriptors are present.

The loop's logic needs to be modified to ensure comprehensive message processing. We want to guarantee that all available messages are retrieved before the function returns, regardless of the number of file descriptors.

A robust solution would involve restructuring the event waiting mechanism to prioritize message queue events and ensure complete message retrieval. This might require rethinking the current event handling strategy to create a more reliable message reception process.

